2025-08-10 14:23:18.927987 | controller | Alias= settings in the [Install] section, and DefaultInstance= for template
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928017 | controller | units). This means they are not meant to be enabled using systemctl.
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928042 | controller |
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928068 | controller | Possible reasons for having this kind of units are:
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928097 | controller | • A unit may be statically enabled by being symlinked from another unit's
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928121 | controller |   .wants/ or .requires/ directory.
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928145 | controller | • A unit's purpose may be to act as a helper for some other unit which has
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928166 | controller |   a requirement dependency on it.
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928190 | controller | • A unit may be started when needed via activation (socket, path, timer,
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928212 | controller |   D-Bus, udev, scripted systemctl call, ...).
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928234 | controller | • In case of template units, the unit is meant to be enabled with some
2025-08-10 14:23:18.928257 | controller |   instance name specified.
